At Ohio Dominican, life is about more than just hitting the books. There is plenty of time and opportunities for fun, friends and enjoying life on campus.
ODU offers 40 undergraduate degrees, 9 graduate programs and more than 20 certificates, licensures and endorsements.
Ohio Dominican is the only NCAA Division II school in Central Ohio, with 16 teams and more than 400 student-athletes.

You'll find plenty of ways to give back while at ODU, including Make a Difference Day, blood drives, food drives, service mission trips to places like Haiti and Appalachia, and local service opportunities.
With 40 high-demand majors available, you’ll have no problem finding a program that matches your passion.
Ohio Dominican students, faculty and staff have free use, year-round, of a fully equipped fitness center.
At ODU, your classmates and professors will know you by name. Trust us, you won’t just be a number.
With small class sizes and personal attention, we'll make sure you succeed in the classroom.

Develop your leadership skills, connect with friends and play an active role in the ODU community.
Students Find Fish Never Before Seen in Alum Creek

An Ohio Dominican University Ichthyology class has found a species of fish in Alum Creek for the first time in history. Environmental Science students utilize the creek regularly as part of their field learning.
